<a id="comment-21135"></a>
<div class="comment">
 <h3 class="title"><a href="node/1733#comment-21135" class="active">Imperative programming has its benefits, too</a></h3>
 <div class="content"><p ><i >On the other hand, starting with a pure functional language maybe is better in the long run, because the programmer's mind is not 'littered' with the imperative model. I think it is easier to go to imperative from functional than the other way around.</i></p>
<p >For lots of beginner-type programming problems (e.g., converting a string to an integer), yes, I agree that pure functional programming would be better.  But there's definitely something to be said for incrementally updating data structures and interactively inspecting them.</p></div>
 <div class="links">By <a href="user/655" title="View user profile.">James Hague</a> at Tue, 09/19/2006 - 13:44 | <a href="user/login">login</a> or <a href="user/register">register</a> to post comments</div>
