<div class="comment">
 <h3 class="title"><a href="node/1733#comment-21137" class="active">Teaching Via Programming</a></h3>
 <div class="content"><p >I think it is worth noting that the ultimate goal of Logo wasn't to teach programming but rather to teach or develop mathematical thinking in kids <i >via</i> programming. I think that the notion of learning via programming can (and should) be extended to other domains. This was the subject of my talk I briefly mentioned <a href="http://lambda-the-ultimate.org/node/1664">here</a>. The approach I envision relies heavily on DSLs, tailored to learning and interacting with specific subjects.</p></div>
 <div class="links">By <a href="user/1" title="View user profile.">Ehud Lamm</a> at Tue, 09/19/2006 - 15:51 | <a href="user/login">login</a> or <a href="user/register">register</a> to post comments</div>
